### 🗺️ The Golden Rule of Imports

```
app/           →  can import from  →  src/
src/           →  NEVER imports from  →  app/
app/page.tsx   →  imports components from  →  src/components/
app/api/route  →  imports logic from  →  src/lib/, src/utils/
```

**RULE:** `app/` is a thin routing shell. Every page file must look like this:

```tsx
// app/dashboard/page.tsx — CORRECT ✅
import { DashboardView } from '@/components/dashboard/DashboardView'
import { getUser } from '@/lib/api/users'

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const user = await getUser()          // ← data fetching from src/lib
  return <DashboardView user={user} />  // ← rendering from src/components
}
```

**NEVER put logic, components, or hooks directly inside `app/` files.**

