## 🧩 Component Rules

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — Named export, typed props, clean JSX
import { cn } from '@/utils/cn'
import type { ButtonHTMLAttributes } from 'react'

interface ButtonProps extends ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost'
  isLoading?: boolean
}

export const Button = ({
  variant = 'primary',
  isLoading = false,
  className,
  children,
  disabled,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium transition-colors',
        variant === 'primary' && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90',
        variant === 'secondary' && 'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80',
        variant === 'ghost' && 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',
        (disabled || isLoading) && 'pointer-events-none opacity-50',
        className
      )}
      disabled={disabled || isLoading}
      aria-busy={isLoading}
      {...props}
    >
      {isLoading ? <span className="mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin" aria-hidden /> : null}
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}
```

- **Named exports only** — never `export default`
- **One component per file** — file name matches component name (PascalCase)
- **Props interface** always defined above the component
- **Extend native HTML element props** when wrapping HTML elements
- **No inline styles** — Tailwind only
- **Use `cn()`** for all conditional class names
- **Add `aria-*` attributes** for accessibility on interactive elements
- **Keep components under 150 lines** — extract sub-components if needed
- **No business logic in components** — delegate to hooks or utils

