## 🔒 Security & Environment Rules

```ts
// src/lib/env.ts — Validate env vars at startup
import { z } from 'zod'

const envSchema = z.object({
  DATABASE_URL: z.string().url(),
  NEXTAUTH_SECRET: z.string().min(32),
  NEXTAUTH_URL: z.string().url(),
  NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL: z.string().url(),
})

export const env = envSchema.parse(process.env)
```

- **Validate ALL env vars** with Zod at startup — fail fast if misconfigured
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` prefix ONLY for values intentionally exposed to the browser
- Never log sensitive values (tokens, passwords, PII)
- Sanitize and validate ALL user input server-side before DB operations
- Use parameterized queries — never string-interpolate SQL
- Rate-limit all public API routes with `@upstash/ratelimit` or similar

