## 🚀 Code Quality Checklist

Before considering any code complete, verify:

- [ ] No TypeScript errors — `pnpm type-check` passes
- [ ] No ESLint warnings — `pnpm lint` passes
- [ ] All new utils/hooks have unit tests
- [ ] No `console.log` statements in production code
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets, URLs, or magic numbers (use `constants/`)
- [ ] Error states are handled and shown to the user
- [ ] Loading states are handled
- [ ] Empty states are handled
- [ ] Component is accessible (keyboard nav, ARIA labels, color contrast)
- [ ] Mobile responsive layout verified

